## 9. CSS Architecture Patterns

### 9.1 Utility-First Approach

**Benefits:**
- Consistent design system
- Rapid prototyping
- Reduced CSS bundle size
- Maintainable styles

**Implementation Pattern:**
```jsx
// Instead of custom CSS classes
className="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-2 bg-white border rounded-lg shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow"
```

### 9.2 Component-Based Styling

**DaisyUI Component Integration:**
- Semantic component classes
- Theme-aware styling
- Consistent design patterns
- Accessibility built-in

### 9.3 Responsive Design Strategy

**Mobile-First Philosophy:**
1. Design for mobile screens first
2. Add desktop enhancements with breakpoint prefixes
3. Use progressive disclosure for complex layouts
4. Maintain usability across all screen sizes

### 9.4 Performance Considerations

**CSS Optimization:**
- PurgeCSS removes unused styles
- Utility classes enable better caching
- Minimal custom CSS reduces bundle size
- Component reusability improves consistency

